body:
I was looking into this issue now, on latest master. From what I can see, `PersonTest` and `PersonFactory` are loaded using Quarkus Runtime ClassLoader, whereas loading of `Person` class from the factory class happens via Quarkus Base Runtime ClassLoader, and that loader throws [here](https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/blob/3.24.3/independent-projects/bootstrap/core/src/main/java/io/quarkus/bootstrap/classloading/QuarkusClassLoader.java#L549):

```
if (classPathResourceIndex.isBanned(resourceName)) {
    throw new ClassNotFoundException(name);
}
```

`Person` class is banned in the base runtime classloader since it's marked as reloadable.

I will continue looking into it and try to understand what changed from 3.22.0 to 3.23.0 that caused this. I'm not an expert in this topic, so most likely I might need to validate it with more experienced folks in Zulip, and it may take a bit of time. You should get an update soon, @celcius112 .
